    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1205</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Shukla, Nishanshi Atulkumar</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The main contribution of this submission is an evaluation framework for digital storytelling in trustworthy AI.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The three paragraphs of this abstract do not present a cohesive argument. While all three make sense individually, how well they work together is not clear.&#10;The abstract will benefit from reducing generalizations and including more specificity on how the topic presented in the title is achieved in the proposed paper.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The paragraph might make more sense after reviewing the figures mentioned in the abstract.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">56</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1311</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Li, Simin</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1. The abstract lists two figures but I cannot see them. I am interested in 2021&#039;s digital storytelling practice but the abstract did not provide more detail. &#10;&#10;2. The topic is significant and I think the research can provide some implications for the evaluation framework in library&#039;s AI application in storytelling. &#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">60</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1198</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Visa, Sofia</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Paper explores the elements of trust in and satisfaction with stories created by humans in collaborations with generative AI tools.&#10;&#10;I could only read the abstract. Where is the entire paper? Where are Figures 1 and 2? &#10;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Paper explores the elements of trust in and satisfaction with stories created by humans in collaborations with generative AI tools.&#10;&#10;I could only read the abstract. Where is the entire paper? Where are Figures 1 and 2? &#10;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
