    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">UTC +1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">4</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">88.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">100.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">76.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">107</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1233</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Kashyap, Deepika</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper explains how the everyday use of digital platforms by citizens in China offers dynamic insights into Chinese nationalism. Based on the two Chinese digital platforms, the author argues that the digital actors of these platforms constantly negotiate between their online and offline selves. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The author has clearly outlined the cause of the changing nationalist discourse in China. To examine the interplay between digital platforms and changing nationalist discourse in China, the author has employed both online and offline ethnography. &#10;Both theoretically and methodologically, the author has tried to do all the justice to the paper. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I am impressed by the paper. The author clearly outlined all the details about the study in the paper. Also, the author demonstrated very good knowledge of the subject. The paper has a clear argument, theoretical background, and methodologies. I strongly recommend this paper for this conference.  </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">100</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1052</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Coghill, KáLyn</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Your investigation into how Chinese nationalist discourses are reshaped online provides a comprehensive look into the dynamics of national sentiment on the Internet. Your ethnographic approach using Sina Weibo and bilibili as field sites offers valuable insights into the daily (re)generation of Chinese national identity.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Your study benefits from several strengths, including a rich data set from an extensive observation period and detailed field notes, which offer a solid foundation for understanding nuanced interactions and discourses. Additionally, by highlighting the role of ordinary users in shaping nationalist discourse, the study adds significant depth to the analysis of online nationalism. Incorporating technical and socio-political contexts further enriches the interpretation of how discourses are formed and transformed. However, there are areas for improvement. It would be beneficial to clarify the ethnographic approach by detailing the criteria for observing and selecting nationalist discourses, providing a clearer picture of the observation process. Expanding on how user interactions influence discourse could also offer deeper insights into the socio-political landscape on these platforms. Finally, addressing any limitations or biases in the data collection and analysis is crucial. This will help to strengthen the findings.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">88</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1311</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Li, Simin</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">the abstract may not discloses much the definition/concept of consumerism and fandom but the author should explain them in the paper</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
