    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Arizona State University</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">United States of America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North_America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"> </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">amnoguer@asu.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">amnoguer@asu.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Noguera-Henao, Andrea</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">amnoguer@asu.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I will be presenting from the Mountain Standard Time (MST) zone, as I live in Phoenix, Arizona</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">37.3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">56.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">24.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">2</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">108</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1018</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Monzó-Nebot, Esther</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Presents a webpage dedicated to disseminating a doctoral dissertation</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The proposal stresses the need to disseminate research results among a broad audience, especially non-experts. This proposal aligns with scholarship on the benefits of and the right of the public to receive information in plain language, and with proposals harnessing the potential of technology to engage with a wide audience. However, the specific terms of the proposal are only vaguely outlined. A conference attendee may find it difficult to assess its interest, especially when competing with other presentations being held simultaneously.&#10;I would recommend the author(s) to specify the methods, which are now only superficially addressed (“presentando la información de manera simplificada e interactiva”); to clarify the concepts (rather than the authors) used in developing the proposal for the general public (rather than in the dissertation itself); and to argue for the advantages of both concepts and methods. &#10;To sum up, I agree that the idea is relevant, but the abstract presents the project as underdeveloped and may fail to attract the attention of conference attendees. &#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">24</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1125</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Isasi, Jennifer</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This work, requested to be presented as an alternative format, proposes the presentation of the creation of an open access web page with the content of a dissertation that focuses, I understand, on contemporary Colombian literature, in English, and with the goal of opening up literary analysis to a larger audience beyond the university. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">El proyecto de crear una página web, abierta al público sin coste, para aprender sobre la literatura colombiana contemporánea y, en particular, su representación del trauma y duelo en obras autobiográficas es una excelente e importante forma de contribuir a la creación de recursos digitales y poner al alcance de más personas una pequeña parte del patrimonio cultural digital hispanoamericano. Acercar una investigación académica a un público más general es de gran ayuda. Además, contribuirá a la difusión de la historia contemporánea y la representación cultural de hechos históricos a través de la literatura, algo sin duda muy necesario. &#10;&#10;No obstante, la propuesta en concreto carece de información clave para la creación de la web y su contribución a las humanidades digitales. En concreto, esta y futuras propuestas se beneficiarían al presentar y entrar en conversación con los métodos pedagógicos en los que se va a apoyar la presentación de la investigación de estas obras autobiográficas. Por ejemplo, ¿en qué principios pedagógicos se apoya? ¿Van a ofrecerse ejercicios pedagógicos para diferentes audiencias y para que la lectura de la crítica literaria dé el paso a cambios en las prácticas sociales? Además, apuntar claramente quién es la audiencia principal de este recursos web sería importante. ¿Qué tipo de interactividad plantea entre el contenido y los visitantes a la página? </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposal is, unfortunately, not clear enough on its connection to the overall intention of the conference. I love to see presentations in Spanish and about literature in Latin America, and this one in particular touches on a very relevant topic to social justice, that of trauma communicated on autobiographies. However, it doesn&#039;t indicate much on the method(s) followed to transfer a dissertation into a web for an (unclear) audience. On its literary analysis, I have no doubt that the presenter has done a marvelous work, but DH wise, it lacks information. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">56</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1250</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Gauthereau, Lorena</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This presentation will discuss the project of uploading the author&#039;s dissertation to an open website in order to present literary criticism in an interactive manner to a wider audience. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The availability of literary criticism in an interactive website has the potential for theoretical engagement. There are two projects in this abstract: 1) the dissertation itself, and 2) the process of creating an interactive work of literary criticism. From the abstract, I am not sure which is the project being discussed or how the dissertation text itself engages with DH. The theory listed seems to be what is included in the dissertation, but what sort of DH theory is applied in the creation of a digital interactive text?&#10;&#10; I think it would be interesting to learn about the steps taken to not just upload the text onto a site, but how it is transformed into an interactive text. For example: Did the author create a dataset from the research? Was this dataset used to create visualizations that enhance the dissertation text? Were there accessibility concerns? And if so, how were they addressed? How does this project go beyond uploading a text to the web?</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I suggest giving this author an opportunity to revise and resubmit their presentation. It appears they may be new to DH and need some guidance. If they revise, the committee can decide if it should be a poster or a lightning talk presentation, depending on their theoretical engagement. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">32</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
