    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Sexual Violence Online: Digitized Rape and Other Forms of Digital Assault</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">social media, technology facilitated violence against women, online gender-based violence, digital criminology</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;Critical Ethnic Studies&#10;North America&#10;Contemporary&#10;digital activism and advocacy&#10;social media analysis and methods&#10;African American/Black Studies&#10;Communication studies&#10;Feminist studies&#10;Gender and sexuality studies&#10;Law and legal studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">digital activism and advocacy&#10;social media analysis and methods</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Critical Ethnic Studies&#10;African American/Black Studies&#10;Communication studies&#10;Feminist studies&#10;Gender and sexuality studies&#10;Law and legal studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;This poster presentation explores the manifestation of sexual violence in the digital space, focusing on three critical areas: the use of AI technology, specifically Deepfake, to produce digitized rape; doxxing; and revenge porn. It delves into how these forms of digital sexual violence affect survivors, examining the psychological, social, and legal impacts. By analyzing these issues, the presentation aims to shed light on the pervasive nature of sexual violence in the digital era and the urgent need for comprehensive measures to support and protect survivors in online environments.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This poster presentation explores the manifestation of sexual violence in the digital space, focusing on three critical areas: the use of AI technology, specifically Deepfake, to produce digitized rape; doxxing; and revenge porn. It delves into how these forms of digital sexual violence affect survivors, examining the psychological, social, and legal impacts. By analyzing these issues, the presentation aims to shed light on the pervasive nature of sexual violence in the digital era and the urgent need for comprehensive measures to support and protect survivors in online environments.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Coghill, KáLyn</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Virginia Commonwealth University</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">United States of America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North_America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"> </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">COGHILLK@VCU.EDU</ss:Data></Cell>
