    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">46.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">2</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">132</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1023</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Esmaeili, Niloufar</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This poster proposal focuses on a significant and relevant topic for the conference, emphasising the digital forms of sexual violence and how survivors are affected. The relevant themes of critical studies and intersectional feminism are evident in the proposal. However, it lacks specificity in several key areas, which limits its overall strength.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposal discusses a relevant topic in the field of humanities. It would benefit significantly from addressing the following points:&#10;&#10;What specific platform(s) or digital environments will be examined?&#10;What theoretical framework(s) will be used to analyze the data?&#10;How is the data on these forms of digital sexual violence being collected and documented?&#10;Who are the victims/survivors being studied, and how are they identified or categorized?&#10;&#10;Additionally, to enhance the proposal:&#10;Describe the visual components planned for the poster to convey the research results clearly.&#10;Highlight how this study contributes to the existing research on digital sexual violence.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposal highlights a subject that fits well with the themes of the conference. However, its lack of specificity raises concerns about the depth and practicality of the research.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">56</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1018</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Monzó-Nebot, Esther</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The proposal addresses a major problem, the uses of AI technology in representing, perpetuating, and normalizing violence against women.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The proposal addresses a major problem, the uses of AI technology in representing, perpetuating, and normalizing violence against women. The topic is highly relevant, addressing contemporary issues of digital sexual violence, which is a critical and timely subject.&#10;While the abstract clearly outlines the key areas of investigation—AI technology (specifically Deepfake), doxxing, and revenge porn—it could benefit from more specific examples or data points to illustrate the extent of the issues. For example, mentioning recent studies or statistics related to Deepfake or revenge porn incidents would provide a stronger foundation. &#10;Regarding the scope of the proposal, the abstract mentions psychological, social, and legal impacts, indicating a thorough and multifaceted approach. However, it does not detail how these areas will be explored. Including a brief mention of the research methods or theoretical frameworks would enable conference attendees to better understand what to expect from the presentation. For example, will the analysis be qualitative, quantitative, or a mix of both? What sources will be explored? Will intersectional issues be further explored?&#10;To sum up, the proposal outlined in the abstract is promising and addresses significant issues in the digital age. This reviewer recommends incorporating more specific details and adding information about research methods, theoretical approaches, and implications.&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">46</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1091</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Beverly-Porter, Diamond</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The main contribution of this proposal is the illumination of a growing concern in regards to technology and sexual violence. there is a lack of current research addressing AI, Deep Fakes, and doxing in digital space. This proposal seeks to bridge the gap in literature while adhering to the conference theme. is The proposal is organized effectively and offers a clear articulation of presentation content.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposal bridges a gap in literature and research regarding technology and digital spaces. This submission could be improved by considering how the following scholars are currently examining violence in online spaces and connect with your proposal. &#10;&#10;1.) Noble, Safiya Umoja. Algorithms of Oppression : How Search Engines Reinforce Racism. New York University Press, 2018, https://doi.org/10.18574/9781479833641.  &#10;&#10;2.) Wade, Ashleigh Greene. Black Girl Autopoetics: Agency in Everyday Digital Practice. Duke University Press, 2023.  </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">88</ss:Data></Cell>
