    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Using Digital Humanities approaches in Literary Studies: A Case Study of studying #StoptheBeautytest Campaign by Dove</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Digital Humanities, Digital Storytelling, Hashtag Narratives, Digital techniques, post-modernist literary perspective</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;Experimental Humanities&#10;Asia&#10;Contemporary&#10;artificial intelligence and machine learning&#10;social media analysis and methods&#10;user experience design and analysis&#10;Communication studies&#10;Cultural studies&#10;Literary studies&#10;Media studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Asia</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">artificial intelligence and machine learning&#10;social media analysis and methods&#10;user experience design and analysis</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Experimental Humanities&#10;Communication studies&#10;Cultural studies&#10;Literary studies&#10;Media studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;Technological development is changing the course of action in all domains of human existence. And literary studies are also adapting to the technological change by adopting Digital Humanities approaches in its studies. Famous publication houses like Oxford, Palgrave and number of University Presses actively publish titles dealing with the meaning, scope and significance of Digital Humanities and its use in the domain of literary studies. While wonderful scholars like David M. Berry, Eileen Gardiner and Ronald Musto, Nidhi Jindal among others have worked extensively on defining Digital Humanities, there is less scholarly work that lays out the actual process of using Digital Humanities approaches in studying a text. The word ‘text’ itself has evolved in number of ways and now encompasses cartoons, memes, social media narratives, digital stories, and electronic literature. To lay out a step-by-step approach to use Digital Humanities framework in studying a hashtag campaign started by a popular beauty brand, the following paper attempts to study the digital story video posted by Dove on its YouTube handle. Using digital techniques, like exporting comments and using free AI powered software like ChatGPT and MAXQDA, the paper will provide a case study of studying the digital storytelling narrative initiated by Dove, the socio-commercial motive behind highlighting the issue of pre-defined beauty standards in the Indian subcontinent and analyze the possible affect it created on its viewers by expediating the most popular comments on the video. Adopting a post-modernist literary framework, the outlined study aims to provides a hands-on guide of using Digital Humanities approaches in studying a varied text and wants to respond to questions of the significance of using DH in studying newly emerging texts in a more concrete and practical way.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Technological development is changing the course of action in all domains of human existence. And literary studies are also adapting to the technological change by adopting Digital Humanities approaches in its studies. Famous publication houses like Oxford, Palgrave and number of University Presses actively publish titles dealing with the meaning, scope and significance of Digital Humanities and its use in the domain of literary studies. While wonderful scholars like David M. Berry, Eileen Gardiner and Ronald Musto, Nidhi Jindal among others have worked extensively on defining Digital Humanities, there is less scholarly work that lays out the actual process of using Digital Humanities approaches in studying a text. The word ‘text’ itself has evolved in number of ways and now encompasses cartoons, memes, social media narratives, digital stories, and electronic literature. To lay out a step-by-step approach to use Digital Humanities framework in studying a hashtag campaign started by a popular beauty brand, the following paper attempts to study the digital story video posted by Dove on its YouTube handle. Using digital techniques, like exporting comments and using free AI powered software like ChatGPT and MAXQDA, the paper will provide a case study of studying the digital storytelling narrative initiated by Dove, the socio-commercial motive behind highlighting the issue of pre-defined beauty standards in the Indian subcontinent and analyze the possible affect it created on its viewers by expediating the most popular comments on the video. Adopting a post-modernist literary framework, the outlined study aims to provides a hands-on guide of using Digital Humanities approaches in studying a varied text and wants to respond to questions of the significance of using DH in studying newly emerging texts in a more concrete and practical way.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
