    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">146</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1168</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Twani, Khanyisa</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">An interesting paper on analysing brand campaigns through social media, and perhaps it&#039;s effects since the author will include audience comments on the campaign. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The submission is well explained, however minor details can be included to boost the overall &quot;packaging&quot; of the work.&#10;The author can thus include the following:&#10;- Formal citations, &#10;- a less &quot;generalistic&quot; purpose of the work where author &quot;wants to respond to questions of significance of using DH...&quot; to make it more aligned because DH is already quite broad in itself. &#10;These are suggested to ensure a more well rounded submission. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">64</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1180</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Karajgikar, Jajwalya</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">While I agree that the concept of &quot;text&quot; being more ubiquitously multimodal is important, I have some reservations regarding the statement &quot;less scholarly work that lays out the actual process of using Digital Humanities approaches in studying a text.&quot; From Miriam Posner&#039;s work to Melanie Walsh&#039;s to projects like the Data-Sitter&#039;s Club, and so much more, there is a lot of work on the steps and process of a DH Computational Text Analysis project.&#10;The steps being taken seem to be more along the lines of qualitative research rather than computational text analysis, unless I am misunderstanding the abstract. I commend the paper for the subject matter it is dealing with and would be interested in some more clarity around the topic and methodology.&#10;Thank you for sharing your work with us. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I hope my criticism is constructive and meaningful enough for the requisite changes to be made. Please let me know if I need to elaborate any of my points. Thanks.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">58</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1325</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Champagne, Ashley</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This abstract outlines a case study studying a social media campaign by Dove and articulates the wide impact of the field of digital humanities. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The abstract is unfortunately not very focused on the reasoning behind its study and it is unclear what methods the author is using. It is difficult in any short abstract to explain the depth of your research, but this abstract starts so generally about the digital humanities that it reduces the actual substance of what the talk is about to a couple sentences. I also wish the author had explained more what they mean by a &quot;more concrete and practical way.&quot; More concrete and practical by doing what?</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">44</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1003</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Fernandez, Sylvia</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The main contribution of this submission is an analysis of the digital story video posted by Dove and how this narrative defines beauty standards in the Indian subcontinent through a text analysis approach. It also makes a critique of DH  and the lack of text analysis literature.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This submission has great potential and will be benefited from this conference to articulate the methodology and theoretical framework based on previous work done in the digiital humanities. It could show a stronger argument if it focuses in this case study connected to the area of text analysis of beauty narratives instead of approaching a very broad critique of the digital humanities and text analysis in this field. I will recommend the author to be more specific on its arguments and provide references of other case studies that have implemented text analysis of digital story videos. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">46</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">-1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Rejected</ss:Data></Cell>
