    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">153</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1001</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Lach, Pamella R.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper explores questions of ethical data collection, visualization, and analysis related to racial justice movements. Using the Virulent Hate project as its case study, this paper offers ways of engaging in self-reflective and socially-responsible public-facing data curation that would be highly relevant to a broad range of projects.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a thoughtful and thought-provoking submission that promises to explore a range of practices related to ethical data collection/curation within the context of racial justice movements. I appreciate the authors&#039; self-reflective approach, and would be eager to hear some of their lessons learned and better practices for improving data collection, visualization, and public-facing analysis/curation. I would encourage the authors to show how their work can be applied beyond ongoing racial justice movements to other kinds of social justice oriented public humanities work.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">96</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1229</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Adal, Raja</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a reflection by the investigators of the Virulent Hate Project that discusses the various methodological issues adopted by the project.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a coherent reflection on a project.  I don&#039;t know the scope of the Virulent Hate project, but such reflections by the PIs of a project are often interesting and this one seems to be no exception.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">90</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1235</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Poluru, Ramesh</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper considers how Virulent Hate&#039;s documentation process has evolved over the last four years, contending with a prolonged pandemic, a shifting political landscape, and an evolving understanding of the ramifications of our work.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Limited discussion on the methodology and analytical framework.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
