    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Cultural Capital and Expectation: Decoding Failure Narratives in Online Hotel Reviews</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Digital humanities, Cultural capital, Expectation, Failure narrative, Online hotel review</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;North America&#10;Contemporary&#10;cultural analytics&#10;Communication studies&#10;Cultural studies&#10;digital humanities and/in libraries&#10;Digital Storytelling&#10;Data science/data studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">cultural analytics&#10;digital humanities and/in libraries&#10;Digital Storytelling</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Communication studies&#10;Cultural studies&#10;Data science/data studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;This study examines the impact of cultural capital on customer expectations in online reviews from TripAdvisor, Google Reviews, and Booking.com through the &#039;narratives of service failure&#039; in selected themed hotels spread across Las Vegas. The choice of Las Vegas as the focal point for this study is strategically significant due to its status as a global tourism hub, where a diverse international clientele interacts with a wide range of service offerings. This provides a rich context for analyzing varied expressions of cultural capital and customer expectations. Through the theoretical standpoints of Bourdieu&#039;s cultural capital, Burgoon’s expectancy violation theory, and narrative theory, a corpus comprising about 12,000 online reviews were collected for analysis.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Ongoing analysis was carried out using a combination of WebHarvy, NVivo and Voyant tools to uncover a multifaceted relationship between customers&#039; cultural backgrounds, expectations, and their feedback; highlighting how cultural capital fundamentally shapes perceptions of service quality and expectations. The exploration of the interplay between cultural capital, expectation violations, and digital narratives, potentially provides insight into the societal implications of digital communication and customer service. Also to be emphasized is the responsibility of the hospitality sector in recognizing and addressing cultural diversity, framing it not just as a business necessity, but as a societal obligation.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Moreover, the study affirms the invaluable status of digital tools for interpreting and responding to customer narratives, fostering a culture of innovation and accountability in the hospitality industry. The insights from this study will be relevant in steering (themed) hotels towards culturally sensitive and responsive service strategies, ultimately improving customer satisfaction and loyalty in a challenging, post-pandemic environment.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This study examines the impact of cultural capital on customer expectations in online reviews from TripAdvisor, Google Reviews, and Booking.com through the &#039;narratives of service failure&#039; in selected themed hotels spread across Las Vegas. The choice of Las Vegas as the focal point for this study is strategically significant due to its status as a global tourism hub, where a diverse international clientele interacts with a wide range of service offerings. This provides a rich context for analyzing varied expressions of cultural capital and customer expectations. Through the theoretical standpoints of Bourdieu&#039;s cultural capital, Burgoon’s expectancy violation theory, and narrative theory, a corpus comprising about 12,000 online reviews were collected for analysis.&#10;Ongoing analysis was carried out using a combination of WebHarvy, NVivo and Voyant tools to uncover a multifaceted relationship between customers&#039; cultural backgrounds, expectations, and their feedback; highlighting how cultural capital fundamentally shapes perceptions of service quality and expectations. The exploration of the interplay between cultural capital, expectation violations, and digital narratives, potentially provides insight into the societal implications of digital communication and customer service. Also to be emphasized is the responsibility of the hospitality sector in recognizing and addressing cultural diversity, framing it not just as a business necessity, but as a societal obligation.&#10;Moreover, the study affirms the invaluable status of digital tools for interpreting and responding to customer narratives, fostering a culture of innovation and accountability in the hospitality industry. The insights from this study will be relevant in steering (themed) hotels towards culturally sensitive and responsive service strategies, ultimately improving customer satisfaction and loyalty in a challenging, post-pandemic environment.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
