    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">aakinola@mtu.edu, s.adegbenro@ku.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Akinola, Ayodele James;&#10;Adegbenro, Sunday Adesoye</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">aakinola@mtu.edu;&#10;s.adegbenro@ku.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">EST</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">78.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">80.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">76.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">162</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1205</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Shukla, Nishanshi Atulkumar</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The main contribution of this submission is decoding failure narratives in customer reviews for Hotels in Las Vegas.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The abstract it well crafted. It will benefit from explaining what is meant by narratives of service failure and exactly how are they being analyzing. The tools used for analysis are mentioned in the abstract, but the abstract lacks clarity on exactly how these tools are used and what results are obtained. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The authors state major questions they are exploring without giving the results of their study. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">78</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1311</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Li, Simin</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I can see the innovative research design, interdisciplinary research, multiple theories, and a meaningful topic in the proposal. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">If the author can add the reason why cultural capital is the focus of the research may be more convincible. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">76</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1168</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Twani, Khanyisa</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The submission is about data analysis on service failure(s) in Las Vegas hospitality industry, specifically hotels with international clientele using relevant analytical tools within the DH field. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The submission seems to have a strong focus on data science in commercial aspects of cultural studies. The submission can be further improved with a clear indication of how the work is applicable and/or relevant to the aspect of DH in libraries which does not come through quite explicitly in the abstract. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">80</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">-1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Rejected</ss:Data></Cell>
