    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Graham, Meredith C.;&#10;Lach, Pamella R.;&#10;East, Grace;&#10;Caomhanach, Nuala;&#10;Cox, Lauren Burrell;&#10;Ke, June;&#10;Tanks, Cassie;&#10;Martinez, Priscilla</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">graham.meredithclaire@gmail.com;&#10;plach@sdsu.edu;&#10;its.grace.east@gmail.com;&#10;nfc231@nyu.edu;&#10;lauren-cox@uiowa.edu;&#10;wk2259@nyu.edu;&#10;tanks.c@northeastern.edu;&#10;priscilla.martinez2@utsa.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">We span the entire continental United States (from Pacific to Eastern) PLUS Shanghai</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">86.7</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">96.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">72.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">166</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1114</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">O&#039;Neil, Erica</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This alternative session recreates their successful podcasting institutes&#039; &quot;listening parties.&quot; This will feature both a project parade and the context to understand how graduate students crafted those products to create &quot;public-facing, digitally-inflected, and community-engaged&quot; products that adhere to an emergent humanities strategy that transforms scholarly praxis. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">An alternative session is well-suited to the convey the experiential knowledge gains centered in this team- and care-based model of learning. Very keen on learning more about the process as well as the products, which are both well-detailed in this proposal.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">92</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1081</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Haines, Chelsea</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This submission offers participants the opportunity to become acquainted with podcasting as a tool for new kinds of humanities scholarship based on collaboration and dialogue.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This submission proposes an innovative and engaging mode for thinking about how to present and disseminate humanities based work through podcasts that highlights collaboration and dialogue. The proposed format of engaging participants by listening to podcast clips and offering a space for discussion is compelling, and could be further enhanced by proposing opportunities for participants to also become authors/podcasters themselves.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">72</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1163</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Nguyen, Cindy Anh</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">showcasing the podcasting institute as a combination of digital humanities methods through Adrienne marie browns&#039;s Emergent Strategy: Shaping Change, Changing Worlds. Invites in opportunity to learn and think through podcasting for values based learning and community building </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Everything is strong for this proposal, although I would have liked a bit more concreteness on how emergent strategy might look like in the alternative format (for example, a few methods, approaches, findings to highlight from the successes/limitations of past institutes)</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">96</ss:Data></Cell>
