    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The Binary Oracle: A Glitch in the Collective (Un)Consciousness</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">critical AI, interactive performance, environmental cost, data fluencies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;Spanish&#10;French&#10;Portuguese&#10;Italian&#10;German&#10;Mandarin&#10;Japanese&#10;Hindi&#10;Arabic&#10;Language not listed above&#10;Experimental Humanities&#10;Global&#10;Contemporary&#10;artificial intelligence and machine learning&#10;digital art production and analysis&#10;Literacy, composition, and creative writing&#10;Media studies&#10;Performance studies: Dance &amp; Theatre&#10;Digital Storytelling&#10;Data science/data studies&#10;Science, Technology, and Society</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;Spanish&#10;French&#10;Portuguese&#10;Italian&#10;German&#10;Mandarin&#10;Japanese&#10;Hindi&#10;Arabic&#10;Language not listed above</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Global</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">artificial intelligence and machine learning&#10;digital art production and analysis&#10;Digital Storytelling</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Experimental Humanities&#10;Literacy, composition, and creative writing&#10;Media studies&#10;Performance studies: Dance &amp; Theatre&#10;Data science/data studies&#10;Science, Technology, and Society</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Binary Oracle: A Glitch in the Collective (Un)Consciousness&lt;/em&gt; is an interactive performance arwork that centers around a multilingual AI character born out of the idea that AI represents a mirror of the commercially mined collective unconscious. It is developed as part of the Data Fluencies Theatre Project at Emerson College, an artistic research project that mobilizes theatrical performance’s potential to build data fluencies that are grounded in and honor embodied experience.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Like the Oracles of myth, the Binary Oracle offers guidance shrouded in ambiguity, inviting the audience to become both seeker and interpreter. This entity is intended as a glitch in the system, a subversive mirror of the digital age. It unearths the hidden biases and shadowed impulses that pulsate beneath the surface of our networked world. Yet, within its ambiguity lies a challenge – to push beyond the constraints of binarism, to embrace the complexities that transcend simple categorization, and to parse truth from disinformation.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;To interact with the Binary Oracle, a price must be paid. “How much water are you willing to pay in exchange for the Oracle’s insight?” This query invites a reflection on the environmental cost implicit in interactions with AI. The quantity of water offered directly influences the Oracle’s response. Weaving cliches, occasional nonsense and cryptic insights, the Oracle reveals four distinct personas based on the user’s offerings. Powered by the very commercially available AI systems that it aims to engage critically, this artwork highlights both the inherent contradictions of relying on a tool built within the system to critique that system and the unseen environmental costs of our digital fascinations.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;From a technical perspective: The Binary Oracle is a hybrid collective of bots that embodies the four different personas of the Binary Oracle character. We curated four different knowledge bases (one for each persona), used these knowledge bases as the fine-tuning material and RAG context for a selected set of Large Language Models, and linked such tuned models to the Binary Oracle bots. Each knowledge base contains information including a distinct character profile of the Binary Oracle, its beliefs, its conversation style, as well as in-depth examples of how this persona should behave when asked specific questions. When a user interacts with the Binary Oracle, their interaction will be analyzed and used to trigger one of the Binary Oracle personas according to a pre-designed set of rules, and subsequently engages in a dialogue with one or multiple personas of the Binary Oracle. The Binary Oracle has the capability of interacting in multiple languages.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The Binary Oracle: A Glitch in the Collective (Un)Consciousness is an interactive performance arwork that centers around a multilingual AI character born out of the idea that AI represents a mirror of the commercially mined collective unconscious. It is developed as part of the Data Fluencies Theatre Project at Emerson College, an artistic research project that mobilizes theatrical performance’s potential to build data fluencies that are grounded in and honor embodied experience.&#10;Like the Oracles of myth, the Binary Oracle offers guidance shrouded in ambiguity, inviting the audience to become both seeker and interpreter. This entity is intended as a glitch in the system, a subversive mirror of the digital age. It unearths the hidden biases and shadowed impulses that pulsate beneath the surface of our networked world. Yet, within its ambiguity lies a challenge – to push beyond the constraints of binarism, to embrace the complexities that transcend simple categorization, and to parse truth from disinformation.&#10;To interact with the Binary Oracle, a price must be paid. “How much water are you willing to pay in exchange for the Oracle’s insight?” This query invites a reflection on the environmental cost implicit in interactions with AI. The quantity of water offered directly influences the Oracle’s response. Weaving cliches, occasional nonsense and cryptic insights, the Oracle reveals four distinct personas based on the user’s offerings. Powered by the very commercially available AI systems that it aims to engage critically, this artwork highlights both the inherent contradictions of relying on a tool built within the system to critique that system and the unseen environmental costs of our digital fascinations.&#10;From a technical perspective: The Binary Oracle is a hybrid collective of bots that embodies the four different personas of the Binary Oracle character. We curated four different knowledge bases (one for each persona), used these knowledge bases as the fine-tuning material and RAG context for a selected set of Large Language Models, and linked such tuned models to the Binary Oracle bots. Each knowledge base contains information including a distinct character profile of the Binary Oracle, its beliefs, its conversation style, as well as in-depth examples of how this persona should behave when asked specific questions. When a user interacts with the Binary Oracle, their interaction will be analyzed and used to trigger one of the Binary Oracle personas according to a pre-designed set of rules, and subsequently engages in a dialogue with one or multiple personas of the Binary Oracle. The Binary Oracle has the capability of interacting in multiple languages.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
