    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Tool of Hope or Horror? Why AI Needs Ethicists and Humanists</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">ethics, invention, AI, machine learning</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;Experimental Humanities&#10;North America&#10;Contemporary&#10;artificial intelligence and machine learning&#10;meta-criticism (reflections on digital humanities and humanities computing)&#10;Computer science&#10;History of Science&#10;Humanities Computing&#10;Philosophy&#10;Science, Technology, and Society</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">artificial intelligence and machine learning&#10;meta-criticism (reflections on digital humanities and humanities computing)</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Experimental Humanities&#10;Computer science&#10;History of Science&#10;Humanities Computing&#10;Philosophy&#10;Science, Technology, and Society</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;Every human invention and tool has the potential to benefit or harm humanity, and artificial intelligence is no different. The boon of information and knowledge that came with printing on large scales also brought with it the possibility of libel and disinformation, and societies formulated laws against such practices. Firearms allowed for easier hunting of animals, but also easier elimination of human enemies, and (though hotly contested in some places) governments regulate weapons to assure maximum safety of all concerned. Medical treatments give us myriad ways to be kept alive, but we rightly debate under what circumstances patients should be allowed to refuse treatment. In each of these instances, people well-versed in the history of the matter at hand, the differences in human values, and the shared goals of humanity are essential.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Artificial intelligence is no different. Machine learning, creation of complex models, and high-speed calculation capabilities have enhanced our creativity, efficiency, and productivity. However, AI can just as easily create poisons as it can create life-saving medications, and a tool that can bring efficiency can also create waves of job loss. (See B. Christian’s &lt;em&gt;The Alignment Problem: Machine Learning and Human Values&lt;/em&gt; and V. Eubanks’ &lt;em&gt;Automating Inequality: How High-Tech Tools Profile, Police, and Punish the Poor&lt;/em&gt;). Those who are knowledgeable about the history of technology and the moral judgments surrounding our inventions will play a crucial role moving forward.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Every human invention and tool has the potential to benefit or harm humanity, and artificial intelligence is no different. The boon of information and knowledge that came with printing on large scales also brought with it the possibility of libel and disinformation, and societies formulated laws against such practices. Firearms allowed for easier hunting of animals, but also easier elimination of human enemies, and (though hotly contested in some places) governments regulate weapons to assure maximum safety of all concerned. Medical treatments give us myriad ways to be kept alive, but we rightly debate under what circumstances patients should be allowed to refuse treatment. In each of these instances, people well-versed in the history of the matter at hand, the differences in human values, and the shared goals of humanity are essential.&#10;Artificial intelligence is no different. Machine learning, creation of complex models, and high-speed calculation capabilities have enhanced our creativity, efficiency, and productivity. However, AI can just as easily create poisons as it can create life-saving medications, and a tool that can bring efficiency can also create waves of job loss. (See B. Christian’s The Alignment Problem: Machine Learning and Human Values and V. Eubanks’ Automating Inequality: How High-Tech Tools Profile, Police, and Punish the Poor). Those who are knowledgeable about the history of technology and the moral judgments surrounding our inventions will play a crucial role moving forward.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Huskey, Rebecca K.</ss:Data></Cell>
