    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">174</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1177</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Clawson, Corey</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The proposed panel discuss their approaches to developing the repository Concientizando Comunidades Colectiva.  This archival project addresses the need to fill gaps in knowledge as well as digital and analog archives by preserving and highlighting the contributions of women at the Mexico/US borders who contributed to education, organization, and consciousness raising efforts. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The proposed panel offers a rich and diverse set of approaches to the silences it highlights and addresses. With methods ranging from oral history to mija archival methods and objects of study from festivals to social movements, the panel showcases a diversity of approaches unified around an effort to push against extractive archival approaches while surfacing histories of women organizing and educating at the border. The proposal explicitly outlines this significance, particularly the colectiva&#039;s potential to offer models for scholars pursuing recuperative work with transnational as well as public humanities dimensions. I&#039;m eager to learn more about the archive and the challenges of presenting the repository as a cohesive interconnected project. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">100</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1141</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Dabrowska, Monika</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The panel discusses the multimodal digital repository project that recovers the archives and memories of San Antonio&#039;s women leaders and activists. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The submission highlights women&#039;s roles and women&#039;s participation in community leadership movements and activism. The study of the problem is interesting for the digital humanities community and relevant to the theme of the Conference. I suggest that methodological approach needs to be further clarified (what is understood by “feminist praxis”?) and more details regarding the use of techniques of text analysis are precised and added to the work: e.g., which tool and software is used to perform such repository?, document formats, items selection criteria, data curation, possibilities and limitations of the collection, etc. ? In short, I think there are ways that the proposal can be claryfied and improved.&#10;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">76</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1310</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Alvarez, Maira Elizabeth</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This panel will discuss the process, objectives, and ethics of building a digital repository that aims to document, preserve, and provide access to the contributions of women within education, public policy, and social movements that have influenced communities in Texas and across the border.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The proposal offers various methods to address colonial violence, ranging from oral history to personal archives. It would be a valuable addition to ACH 2024 due to its coverage of various ACH topics.&#10;&#10;One suggestion I have for the authors is to directly address the language component mentioned in the title, specifically the mention of &quot;responsibly [to] create translingual community archives in Texas.&quot; The proposal does not touch upon the translingual component and how it is addressed in the various methods mentioned.&#10;&#10;Additionally, it would be beneficial to clarify the authors&#039; interpretation of &quot;feminist praxis,&quot; as this could be understood differently by fields and individuals.&#10;&#10;Overall, I look forward to learn more about the development of the repository &quot;Concientizando Comunidades Colectiva,&quot; including the challenges it faced, how these challenges were overcome, and what the future holds for the repository.&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This would be a great addition to the ACH conference.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">88</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">9</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Accept as Panel</ss:Data></Cell>
