    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Honest Abe&#039;s Information Emporium: Translating the Gettysburg Address into Multiple Languages with Artificial Intelligence</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">artificial intelligence, AI, deepfakes, history, digital humanities</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;North America&#10;Contemporary&#10;artificial intelligence and machine learning&#10;public humanities collaborations and methods&#10;History&#10;Digital Storytelling&#10;Science, Technology, and Society</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">artificial intelligence and machine learning&#10;public humanities collaborations and methods&#10;Digital Storytelling</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">History&#10;Science, Technology, and Society</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;In this paper, I will describe my experience designing and publishing a digital humanities project called &quot;Honest Abe&#039;s Information Emporium&quot; &lt;https://honestabes.info/&gt;. Funded in part with a grant from the Digital Literacy Accelerator at the United States Department of Education, this project examines the rise of artificial intelligence (AI) and its potential implications for the historical record. The project culminates with a three-minute video of deepfake Abraham Lincoln reciting the Gettysburg Address in nine different language. The first goal of this project is to promote AI literacy among numerous populations, regardless of which language they speak. The second goal is to identify whether the Digital Humanities community can leverage AI for educational, artistic, or political purposes. &lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">In this paper, I will describe my experience designing and publishing a digital humanities project called &quot;Honest Abe&#039;s Information Emporium&quot; &lt;https://honestabes.info/&gt;. Funded in part with a grant from the Digital Literacy Accelerator at the United States Department of Education, this project examines the rise of artificial intelligence (AI) and its potential implications for the historical record. The project culminates with a three-minute video of deepfake Abraham Lincoln reciting the Gettysburg Address in nine different language. The first goal of this project is to promote AI literacy among numerous populations, regardless of which language they speak. The second goal is to identify whether the Digital Humanities community can leverage AI for educational, artistic, or political purposes.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Gibson, Abraham</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">University of Texas at San Antonio</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">United States of America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North_America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"> </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">abraham.gibson@utsa.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">agibson12@unl.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">abraham.gibson@utsa.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Gibson, Abraham</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">abraham.gibson@utsa.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
