    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The Algorithm: building public tech literacy through interactive explainers</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">algorithmic amplification; tech literacy; social media and society</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;Global&#10;Contemporary&#10;software development, systems, analysis, and methods&#10;Computer science&#10;Game studies&#10;Digital Storytelling&#10;open educational resources (OER)&#10;Science, Technology, and Society</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Global</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">software development, systems, analysis, and methods&#10;Digital Storytelling&#10;open educational resources (OER)</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Computer science&#10;Game studies&#10;Science, Technology, and Society</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;I will present &quot;The Algorithm&quot;, a project I build with Lujain Ibrahim with the support of a Mozilla Creative Media Award. It&#039;s an interactive simulation demystifying and breaking down algorithmically-curated social media video feeds and recommendations, such as TikTok&#039;s FYP, Instagram Reels, and YouTube Shorts. &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;In The Algorithm, the user is prompted to test a new social media app’s recommender system. In the process, they interact with a video feed (simulating a TikTok interface) that incorporates the user’s initially stated preferences as well as their engagement signals (e.g., likes, reposts), allowing the user to see and understand feedback loops and personalization in real time. Throughout the process, key concepts and debates on algorithmic recommendation and amplification in the fields of law, policy, computer science, and social science are explored, as well as associated dilemmas and trade-offs. &lt;/p&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The interactive experience is accompanied by further reading, resources, and ongoingg work on lesson plans around the topics of algorithmic recommendation and amplification with the aim of providing a comprehensive resource for making the topic more engaging and accessible to a broad public audience. Though we target a broad and open-ended audience, we are specifically interested in reaching teenagers and young audiences who are the primary users and thus recipients of both harms and benefits of such emerging platforms (especially TikTok) and yet too often left out of conversations on digital sovereignty and internet health. &quot;The Algorithm&quot; is now live at https://whatsthealgorithm.com/ &lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I will present &quot;The Algorithm&quot;, a project I build with Lujain Ibrahim with the support of a Mozilla Creative Media Award. It&#039;s an interactive simulation demystifying and breaking down algorithmically-curated social media video feeds and recommendations, such as TikTok&#039;s FYP, Instagram Reels, and YouTube Shorts. &#10;In The Algorithm, the user is prompted to test a new social media app’s recommender system. In the process, they interact with a video feed (simulating a TikTok interface) that incorporates the user’s initially stated preferences as well as their engagement signals (e.g., likes, reposts), allowing the user to see and understand feedback loops and personalization in real time. Throughout the process, key concepts and debates on algorithmic recommendation and amplification in the fields of law, policy, computer science, and social science are explored, as well as associated dilemmas and trade-offs. &#10;The interactive experience is accompanied by further reading, resources, and ongoingg work on lesson plans around the topics of algorithmic recommendation and amplification with the aim of providing a comprehensive resource for making the topic more engaging and accessible to a broad public audience. Though we target a broad and open-ended audience, we are specifically interested in reaching teenagers and young audiences who are the primary users and thus recipients of both harms and benefits of such emerging platforms (especially TikTok) and yet too often left out of conversations on digital sovereignty and internet health. &quot;The Algorithm&quot; is now live at https://whatsthealgorithm.com/</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
