    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">191</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1306</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Yuan, Miaotong</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This online installation tries to explain the logic behind users&#039; behavior and content recommendation algorithms, which offers nice webpage with interactive design.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This online installation tries to explain the logic behind users’ behavior and content recommendation algorithms, which offers nice webpage with interactive design. But it didn&#039;t go deeper, the function of the algorithms is not clear. Suggest adding more layers and more options.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I went through this simulation/game. As an online installation art, maybe not good enough...but for the diversity of our conference, might be a nicely try.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">56</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1316</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Meneses, Luis</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This submission describes an interactive simulation demystifying and breaking down algorithm-generated social media video feeds and recommendations.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The submission is interesting, timely, and relevant. However, it did not clearly state its research questions, conclusions, or methodology.&#10;&#10;How are the key concepts and debates on algorithmic recommendation and amplification in the fields of law, policy, computer science, and social science are explored? These details were not mentioned, and the main argument could have been strengthened by stating the technologies that were used.&#10;&#10;Once I visited the URL provided (https://whatsthealgorithm.com/), I was able to get a better sense of what the abstract is about.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">58</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1196</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Szydlowski, Nick</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposal and the linked project suggest an engaging and thought-provoking way of creating engagement and discussion around the impact of algorithmic content moderation on social media platforms. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I think this is a strong proposal and an engaging project. In a full presentation I would be really interested to hear more about the design decisions that were made on the project and the process that informed those decisions. The question of how people think about and understand recommendation algorithms and other aspects of technology is a really interesting one, and I think this project has the potential to explore some of those issues.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
