    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">United States of America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North_America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"> </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">karina.fitzgerald@asu.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">karina.fitzgerald@asu.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Fitzgerald, Karina Marie</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">karina.fitzgerald@asu.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">AZ (MST at time of conference)</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">60.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">78.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">36.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">193</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1051</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Galvis, Elliot</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The paper proposes an interesting examination of the gaming industry and its resulting strengths and weaknesses for the future of the medium in the face of corporate consolidation. The provided context for contemporary gaming and the corporate side of game production is welcome.&#10;&#10;I would recommend engaging more explicitly with existing scholarship and critique on the industry and gaming. E.g., the submission refers to Cory Doctorrow&#039;s concept of &quot;enshittification&quot; but does not explain its (important) relevance for the analysis proposed or define it explicitly.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">78</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1091</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Beverly-Porter, Diamond</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The main contribution of this proposal is its relevancy to the changing landscape of games and the game industry. However there is a lack of connection to current scholarship and specificity with hypothesis and case study.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposal highlights a changing landscape between game industries and creative resistance. however the proposal is lack in specificity. This submission could be improved by considering:&#10;&#10;1.) What specific studios or companies are you focusing on?&#10;2.) &quot;This preliminary analysis will seek to explore how the history of video game culture and more recent case studies suggest alternate possibilities for the future of gaming.&quot; Are there specific games you are using as your objects of study?&#10;3.) How is the landscape of the games industry being measured?&#10;4.) What existing scholarship regarding games is you paper in conversation with?&#10;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">36</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1327</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Regan, Amanda</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This sounds like a fascinating paper that looks at the effect of mergers on the indie video game industry. At stake is an indie game culture that has allowed games to usher in new diversity. The paper seeks to analyze how the history of video game culture and more recent events shed light on future of gaming. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a strong proposal that clearly outlines the communities being studied and the effect of mergers on this culture. I would love to hear more about the outlines of the analysis. The abstract does a good job of outlining the background and context for your questions and analysis but doesn&#039;t offer any hints at the methodology the author is employing -- although I can glean that from the keywords.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">66</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
