    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">San Diego State University</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">United States of America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North_America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"> </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">stribelhorn@sdsu.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">stribelhorn@sdsu.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Tribelhorn, Sarah</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">stribelhorn@sdsu.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">PST</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">78.7</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">92.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">66.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">195</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1304</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Giselle Pempedjian, Giselle</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The session should help in brainstorming and reflecting on ideas and ways to guide the stakeholders in making ethical and conscientious decisions regarding the use of AI and digital storage.  Thus, the collaboration in collecting ideas should help the development of a comprehensive rubric that addresses the critical issues as of the environmental impact, ethical issues, and social equity. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The focus on current issues such as transparency, fairness, privacy, and sustainability aligns well with ongoing debates in AI ethics and environmental impact. In addition,  highlighting the impact of AI on marginalized communities and ecosystems adds a critical dimension to the assessment, promoting inclusivity and justice. &#10;Some clearer guidelines would have enhanced the rubric&#039;s effectiveness. Also, adding some details on how the rubric will be implemented and understanding its practical application should help.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">66</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1196</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Szydlowski, Nick</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I think that the connection this submissions draws between AI and mining is an absolutely critical one. This is not just a metaphorical connection - the current AI boom is probably best understood as a form of mining, or an extension of mining activities focused on fuel or minerals. I think that working through the implications of that framing would be an important contribution. I also appreciate the idea of using a round table format to address this issue from multiple perspectives.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I really appreciate this proposal, and I would look forward to attending the proposed round table. I think the focus on the connection between AI and mining is fantastic and gets to the heart of the issue in a way that is absolutely needed at this moment. I have some small suggestions around specific language that might help to make sure that readers of the abstract know what to expect from the program. When I first read the title (&quot;Assessing Fair AI Use&quot;), I expected this to be a panel about the copyright issues related to AI, since many LLM developers claim fair use as their justification for ingesting copyrighted material in their models. Maybe something like &quot;Assessing Just AI Use&quot; or &quot;Assessing Equitable AI Use&quot; would avoid that confusion. Looking forward to the roundtable, I would be interested in seeing how the panel discusses the question of digital storage and its environmental impact - is the current AI boom also a moment where libraries start to question our overall footprint in the world&#039;s data centers? Or are our collections just a drop in the ocean (or a pebble in the mine)? And what would it mean for us to scale back - are we ready for information degrowth? Thank you for this proposal - it gives us all a lot to think about.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">92</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1148</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Xiao, Shuang</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This abstract explores the ethical and social equity issues related to AI and its associated technologies in the context of sustainable development. The abstract offers significant practical and academic value. It comprehensively discusses the multifaceted impact of AI technology on the environment and society, and proposes the development of an assessment rubric, providing a practical tool for professionals in related fields.&#10;&#10;The abstract has several strengths: first, the topic is novel and significant, addressing ethical issues concerning resource consumption, environmental impact, and social equity in AI, which are often overlooked in the rapidly evolving tech field. Second, the discussion is thorough and detailed, providing readers with a comprehensive perspective from multiple angles, including resource consumption, environmental impact, and social issues. Additionally, the proposal to develop an assessment rubric for evaluating the ethical and environmental impact of AI and digital storage is highly practical and instructive. Lastly, it clearly outlines specific discussion topics, offering clear directions for rubric development.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This abstract explores the ethical and social equity issues related to AI and its associated technologies in the context of sustainable development. The abstract offers significant practical and academic value. It comprehensively discusses the multifaceted impact of AI technology on the environment and society, and proposes the development of an assessment rubric, providing a practical tool for professionals in related fields.&#10;&#10;The abstract has several strengths: first, the topic is novel and significant, addressing ethical issues concerning resource consumption, environmental impact, and social equity in AI, which are often overlooked in the rapidly evolving tech field. Second, the discussion is thorough and detailed, providing readers with a comprehensive perspective from multiple angles, including resource consumption, environmental impact, and social issues. Additionally, the proposal to develop an assessment rubric for evaluating the ethical and environmental impact of AI and digital storage is highly practical and instructive. Lastly, it clearly outlines specific discussion topics, offering clear directions for rubric development.&#10;&#10;There are also some suggestions for improvement: first, it is recommended to further refine the framework and implementation details of the assessment rubric to enhance its operability. Second, incorporating case studies can more intuitively demonstrate the ethical and social impacts of AI technology, increasing the paper&#039;s persuasiveness and practicality. Moreover, it is suggested to add empirical data to quantify the specific impacts of AI technology on resource consumption, environmental impact, and social equity, enhancing the study&#039;s scientific rigor and credibility. Lastly, it is recommended to strengthen interdisciplinary collaboration with experts in related fields to further enrich the research perspectives and depth.&#10;&#10;Overall, this abstract offers high academic value and practical significance. The proposed assessment rubric concept holds important practical guidance. It is recommended for acceptance, with further refinement and elaboration of relevant content required for the final paper submission.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">78</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
