    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">197</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1248</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Knox, John Thomas</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This contribution describes the process of creating a text corpus using OCR. The poster also describes various forms of text analysis that were used to analyze and describe the corpus for possible end users. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I think this contribution will be of interest to conference participants. However, it&#039;s not clear from the abstract how the process of creating the corpus or the content of the corpus itself align with the conference theme.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I think this contribution will be of interest to participants, but it is not clear how it aligns with the conference theme.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">42</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1289</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Traylor, Jordan</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This poster presents the creation timeline of a text analysis corpus based on a large-scale book digitization project.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The strengths of this poster lie in its attention to the theoretical and technical aspects of digitization and text analysis; these seem to have been all brought together to make a powerful corpus of materials for researchers. Details of these aspects in the project should be of great interest to viewers of this poster. Perhaps one weakness that could be improved is ensuring the &quot;lessons learned&quot; from the project have applicability outside the project itself - were there challenges that other organizations might run into were they to undertake this kind of project? What advice can be gleaned from this project that could guide another one like it?</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">56</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1192</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Rodrigues, Liz</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This poster will share details of a digitization plus NLP workflow for creating a text analysis corpus. I think the incorporation of the NLP stages of this process will be a relatively unique contribution, because so far most library-based projects have focused on the digitization side and less on experimenting with newer tools to enhance research/usage.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Thank you to the authors for sharing this work! I will be excited to see this poster and talk with you about how you implemented NLP post-digitization. The review rubric asks for engagement with scholarship to perhaps a greater degree than currently allowed for in the limited space of the abstract, but I think the practical work outlined here is of self-evident value for those of us engaged with the text analysis workflow. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">82</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1327</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Regan, Amanda</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This poster seeks to outline the process and work behind a digitization project that seeks to take books from the MTSU library and turn them into a corpus that could be run through NLP and NER tools.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I am very interested in hearing more about the stages of this project and think the methods were described well in this abstract. My largest piece of feedback is that I want to know more about the corpus and the ways that the corpus informed the methodology for digitizing and creating entryways into this dataset. What types of volumes are included? How were they selected? I&#039;m also wondering about OCR accuracy and whether that shaped the topics and entities that were extracted from these texts.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">56</ss:Data></Cell>
