    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Sadler, Jesse Robert</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Virginia Tech</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">United States of America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North_America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"> </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">jrsadler@vt.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">jrsadler@vt.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Sadler, Jesse</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">jrsadler@vt.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Eastern Standard</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">77.3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">96.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">64.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">198</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1191</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Giannetti, Francesca</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper explores the use of Quarto to create sustainable scholarly websites in the context of a graduate course in public history.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I am intrigued by the proposed focus on &quot;learning skills over a project-based approach.&quot; The author outlines a long sequence of technologies associated with minimal computing to cover in this Master&#039;s level course. Presumably the emphasis is on learning about the process and less so on a polished final output? I appreciate the author&#039;s stress on maintaining control over the means of production; this is a critical aspect of sustainability. I do wonder what is distinctive about Quarto as opposed to any of several other markdown to HTML workflows and hope the author will give us some insight into this decision.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">72</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1265</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Arbuckle, Alyssa</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This presentation discusses the use of Quarto for developing DH websites, including in a Master&#039;s level course. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This presentation is sure to be of interest to those who are interested in minimal computing, pedagogical approaches to DH, and a cross-section between these groups. It discusses a specific open source publishing tool (Quarto) and provides an example of how this was used as a teaching tool in a Master&#039;s level DH &amp; Public History course. This presentation would be strengthened by introducing a deeper theoretical framework, which could engage topics of preservation, sustainability, minimal computing, open source tools, and pedagogy, or some combination thereof. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">64</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1026</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Kerns, Halie Morgan</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The main contribution would be a walk-through of how to create a minimal DH website using open source tools. This would be valuable for those familiar and unfamiliar alike. It would also outline how to teach the skills and valuable insight students can gain from the project. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a strong and worthwhile  topic. Minimal computing is growing increasingly important in the field and I think many including myself would benefit from seeing how the components come together to create a great DH project and curriculum.  </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">96</ss:Data></Cell>
