    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">86.7</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">94.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">82.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">2</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">2</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">204</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1241</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Ahrenberg, Lars</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The main contribution is an extension of an existing metaphor project (MetaNet Metaphor) to more languages, more varieties and two geographical areas.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is an interesting project of making available a large set of metaphors from several language varieties of English and French. The project has clear theoretical underpinnings and practical applicability and should be of interest to linguists, translators and researchers in cultural studies. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">84</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1237</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Baciu, Dan C.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&quot;Introducing Multilingual MetaNet&quot; by Elise Stickles and Kamal Abou Mikhael offers a significant contribution to the field of linguistics through the creation of a comprehensive, cross-linguistic database for metaphor analysis. By incorporating diverse language varieties, such as African American English, Canadian English and French, and Latin American Spanishes, the project addresses a critical gap in current linguistic research.&#10;&#10;The authors employ robust theoretical frameworks like Conceptual Metaphor Theory and Frame Semantics, combined with advanced NLP techniques, to document semantic and constructional variations. This approach enhances the accuracy of automated metaphor identification and translation, which is a notable achievement.&#10;&#10;The dataset, with over 16,000 example sentences, serves as a valuable reference for linguists, translators, and NLP researchers. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, it promises to be a widely accessible resource. While more detail on specific methodologies and practical applications would strengthen the paper, &quot;Introducing Multilingual MetaNet&quot; is a promising and innovative project that advances our understanding of linguistic diversity and metaphor.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Thank you for the wonderful cross-lingual contribution! I’m looking forward to the finalized presentation. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">82</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1199</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Stevens, Nikki</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The authors are presenting work on an enhanced reference tool for both qualitative research (by linguists and translators) and quantitative computational NLP work.  This tool intervenes in the existing disparities in which certain language vernaculars are better documented and thus more well-studied. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a well-written abstract about an important project. Especially given that this abstract is for a poster, I have no notes for improvement! </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I could see this as a lightning talk rather than a poster - it sounds important! But I defer to the linguists in the community, because that is not me!</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">94</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
