    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Serventi, Jennifer;&#10;Brown, Meaghan;&#10;Hardy, Molly;&#10;Hindley, Meredith;&#10;Walters Cooper, LaQuanda</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">jserventi@neh.gov;&#10;mbrown@neh.gov;&#10;mhardy@neh.gov;&#10;mhindley@neh.gov;&#10;lwalterscooper@neh.gov</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Eastern United States</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">83.3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">94.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">76.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">209</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1111</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Starry, Rachel</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This session enables conference attendees to learn from NEH staff members about new funding opportunities and changes to existing grant programs that support digital humanities scholarship.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposal explains clearly the value of creating space for conversation between NEH staff members and digital humanities practitioners attending this conference, and would be a valuable addition to the conference program. &#10;&#10;I would only have liked to see more information on two items: first, the proposal notes that &quot;This session will build on last year’s “NEH Funding for the Digital Humanities: Finding Your Fit” ACH 2023 conference session&quot; - but what were the outcomes from the previous session? In what ways does this session build on those outcomes? The session title also forefronts &quot;AI&quot; which might be misleading if the focus of the session is on a wide variety of grant programs, only some of which involve the intersection of digital humanities and artificial intelligence.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">80</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1193</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Chassanoff, Alexandra</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This session proposes to share information about the grant programs offered through the National Endowment for the Humanities (NEH).  As a long time supporter of the digital humanities, this roundtable is aimed at keeping scholars and researchers current with grant programs and opportunities. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The proposed session is an informational roundtable with opportunities for audience participation. By sharing information about current grants and changes to programs, this roundtable will help to prepare scholars and researchers for future proposals.  While there are not explicit ties to anti-racist work named in the proposal, raising awareness of potential opportunities for carrying out and sustaining anti-racist scholarship is extremely useful. More information about how audience participation will be incorporated would be useful.  </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">94</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1257</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Burress, Theresa</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This session will provide information about the newest NEH funding opportunities and Endowment-wide special initiatives, and provide updates on changes to longstanding programs that support digital humanities scholarship, pedagogy, public engagement, preservation, and infrastructure development, including those that that expand NEH funding opportunities for historically underserved scholars, communities, and institutions. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is an interesting submission, as it is submitted by a US funding agency regarding opportunities, rather than reporting directly on a research issue. As a round table proposal, it will likely be highly relevant to many audience members and the discussion opportunity in the ACH venue could provide an opportunity for collaborators to find one another. I appreciate NEH&#039;s thoughtful approach to this presentation, and feel that it more than meets the spirit of this conference.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">My only concern is whether the program organizers will have to reject a highly relevant research-focused proposal in favor of this agency-led discussion. However, it appears that this type of programming has been part of the conference in the past, and it could raise awareness about funding opportunities for many scholars who may not be aware of their options, and so I would support providing space in this venue for NEH.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">76</ss:Data></Cell>
