    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I am unable to add the references as they take up too many words in the abstract.&#10;&#10;Elson, D. K., Dames, N., &amp; McKeown, K. R. 2010. Extracting social networks from literary fiction. In J. Hajic, C. Carberry, &amp; S. Clark (Eds.), Proceedings of the 48th Annual Meeting of the Association for Computational Linguistics (138–147). Uppsala, Sweden: Association for Computational Linguistics.&#10;Falk, M. 2016. Making Connections: Network Analysis, the Bildungsroman and the World of The Absentee. Journal of Language, Literature and Culture 63, 2-3 (2016), 107–122.&#10;Krug, M. 2020. Techniques for the Automatic Extraction of Character Networks in German Historic Novels. PhD Dissertation. Julius-Maximilians-Universität Würzburg.&#10;Moretti, F. 2003. Graphs, Maps, Trees: Abstract Models for Literary History. New Left Review, 24, 67-93.&#10;van de Ven, I., Lim, C., Steenbakker, M., &amp; van Zaanen, M. 2018. Negotiating close and distant reading: Heteroglossia and networks in Zadie Smith’s White Teeth. In Digital Humanities Benelux</ss:Data></Cell>
