    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The Art of Social Engagement</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Curation, social justice, visual culture, multidciplinary, Omeka</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;North America&#10;Comparative (2 or more geographical areas)&#10;Contemporary&#10;digital activism and advocacy&#10;digital archiving&#10;African American/Black Studies&#10;Art history&#10;Gender and sexuality studies&#10;History&#10;digital humanities and/in libraries&#10;Border and Transborder studies&#10;Latino/a/x/e Studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North America&#10;Comparative (2 or more geographical areas)</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">digital activism and advocacy&#10;digital archiving&#10;digital humanities and/in libraries</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">African American/Black Studies&#10;Art history&#10;Gender and sexuality studies&#10;History&#10;Border and Transborder studies&#10;Latino/a/x/e Studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;Faculty at Georgia College &amp; State University, the state&#039;s designated public liberal arts institution, are coming together across college and disciplinary boundaries to produce what may be an unprecedented digital exhibit of artwork on themes of social justice from our permanent collections. Entitled Art of Social Engagement, this exhbit organizes a gallery of more than 100 original prints, photographs, ceramic objects, and paintings by major artists and international collaboratives into eight themes of social justice with special content created by faculty and students that examines the work from multidisciplinary perspectives to showcase our liberal arts mission and the university&#039;s digital humanities initiative. The exhibition website, created in Omeka, features contributions in essays, videos, podcasts, data visualizations, and geospatial maps. This talk introduces the exhibit and its unique concept as a model for a project that can be adopted and adapted at other institutions.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Faculty at Georgia College &amp; State University, the state&#039;s designated public liberal arts institution, are coming together across college and disciplinary boundaries to produce what may be an unprecedented digital exhibit of artwork on themes of social justice from our permanent collections. Entitled Art of Social Engagement, this exhbit organizes a gallery of more than 100 original prints, photographs, ceramic objects, and paintings by major artists and international collaboratives into eight themes of social justice with special content created by faculty and students that examines the work from multidisciplinary perspectives to showcase our liberal arts mission and the university&#039;s digital humanities initiative. The exhibition website, created in Omeka, features contributions in essays, videos, podcasts, data visualizations, and geospatial maps. This talk introduces the exhibit and its unique concept as a model for a project that can be adopted and adapted at other institutions.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
