    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">4</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">4</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">85.5</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">94.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">74.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">213</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1129</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Shaarawi, Jihan</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper examines how Palestinian cultural heritage is represented on Instagram by looking at multilingual accounts and hashtags. It identifies common visual themes and textual arguments as well as analyzing the influence of these accounts, their responses to major events, and the relationship between digital posts and material objects. It argues that these digital practices play a crucial role in defining and sharing cultural heritage.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a very relevant and powerful topic. More emphasis on your theoretical framework will provide more context to your paper. Additionally, more details on your method with regards to which hashtags and accounts you chose to follow would be useful. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">86</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1125</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Isasi, Jennifer</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This presentation will showcase an analysis of born-digital invocations of Palestinian cultural heritage on Instagram, by means of identifying content with hashtags and account close readings. It will note heritage themes of regular content as well as interruptions that respond to major events. The main goal is to argue for the study of digital spaces to understand and support the dissemination and preservation of cultural heritage, in particular the Palestinian one, in digital formats. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposal clearly articulates its goals and research focus, and it pairs very well with a few of the main themes of the conference. I look forward to learning more about the findings.&#10;&#10;I believe this will be also a great example of a &quot;new&quot; venue and method for scholars of social media who want to explore Instagram or more visual social media content, now that one of the most studied venue, Twitter, is no longer easily available. &#10;&#10;My only recommendation, and perhaps it is just a matter of lacking space in the abstract, is to make sure to include a section about the process and methods used to identify visual themes and analyze textual material. This includes an explanation of the process used to choose accounts and hashtags (what was included? what was left out? why?). </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">94</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1311</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Li, Simin</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I am impressed by the multi-language accounts analysis of the paper and can&#039;t wait to see the meaning and value of individuals&#039; role on social media and cultural heritage. Also, I wonder the background/motivation of the topic chose by the author. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">74</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1248</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Knox, John Thomas</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The contribution examines how social media and born-digital media inform and shape cultural heritage practices and understanding.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a very timely topic and one that will be of interest to participants. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This sounds like a fascinating project and one that I&#039;m excited to learn more about. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">88</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
