    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&quot;Intankáveis contra o Bostil&quot;: racism, misogyny, and antisemitism in Telegram chats (2020-2023)</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Social Media, Telegram, Topic Modeling, Content Moderation</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Portuguese&#10;Critical Race Studies&#10;Surveillance Studies&#10;South America&#10;Contemporary&#10;natural language processing&#10;social media analysis and methods&#10;text mining and analysis&#10;Feminist studies&#10;Sociology&#10;Latin American studies&#10;Data science/data studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Portuguese</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">South America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">natural language processing&#10;social media analysis and methods&#10;text mining and analysis</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Critical Race Studies&#10;Surveillance Studies&#10;Feminist studies&#10;Sociology&#10;Latin American studies&#10;Data science/data studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;The panel will present findings on the impact of social media architecture, particularly Telegram, on the dissemination of hate speech in Brazil. The aim is to present and analyze the narratives and values expressed in five Brazilian Telegram chats that promote hate against women, Black people, Indigenous people, and Jews. Using computational techniques for data collection and analysis combined with socio-anthropological reflections, the authors implemented a Python solution to manipulate the Telegram API, allowing real-time collection of textual, audiovisual, and image data. The methodological approach includes topic modeling using BERTopic to identify and classify messages by semantic similarity. The study reveals the prevalence of misogynistic, racist, and anti-Semitic discourses, highlighting how these narratives intertwine to form a hateful vision of Brazil. The term &quot;Bostil&quot; emerges as an expression of contempt for the country, associating its woes with its ethnic and social composition. Group members refer to themselves as &quot;intankáveis,&quot; reflecting resistance to the emancipation of minorities. The analysis underscores the need for more effective content moderation measures and an interdisciplinary approach to combating hate speech on the Internet.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The panel will present findings on the impact of social media architecture, particularly Telegram, on the dissemination of hate speech in Brazil. The aim is to present and analyze the narratives and values expressed in five Brazilian Telegram chats that promote hate against women, Black people, Indigenous people, and Jews. Using computational techniques for data collection and analysis combined with socio-anthropological reflections, the authors implemented a Python solution to manipulate the Telegram API, allowing real-time collection of textual, audiovisual, and image data. The methodological approach includes topic modeling using BERTopic to identify and classify messages by semantic similarity. The study reveals the prevalence of misogynistic, racist, and anti-Semitic discourses, highlighting how these narratives intertwine to form a hateful vision of Brazil. The term &quot;Bostil&quot; emerges as an expression of contempt for the country, associating its woes with its ethnic and social composition. Group members refer to themselves as &quot;intankáveis,&quot; reflecting resistance to the emancipation of minorities. The analysis underscores the need for more effective content moderation measures and an interdisciplinary approach to combating hate speech on the Internet.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
