    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Mello. Jr., Lawrence Joseph</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">lmello@fau.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">East</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">58.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">90.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">36.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">218</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1075</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Poole, Carson Leigh</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This has some great insight into the uses and implications of LibGuides as a research tool for academics, people who work in education, and the library system.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I think this is a great proposal for a Lightning Talk. It is succinct and discusses the scope of what can be done using LibGuides. I personally would like to see more about the curation process, but as this is submitted as a lightning talk I think that can be saved to be explored in the future. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">90</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1191</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Giannetti, Francesca</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This lightning talk describes the use of LibGuides by librarians to improve primary source literacy and discovery.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">It&#039;s a leap to describe LibGuides as &quot;innovative.&quot; This is a ubiquitous, proprietary platform in academic libraries. Librarians use them mainly as a tool of convenience, which does have value in terms of getting one&#039;s content on the web. I would expect to see a reference of the Nimble Tents Toolkit Flash Subject Guides (https://nimbletents.github.io/libguide/) documentation, as it is one of the more thoughtful descriptions of using LibGuides in a digital humanities context. The vox populi among librarians is that LibGuides are underutilized, even ignored by their target readership, so the author will need to dig deeper to counter the perception that they do little to enhance source discoverability.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">36</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1176</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Agostini, Caterina</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper examines the significance and applications of LibGuides in research and teaching.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper examines the significance and applications of LibGuides in research and teaching. Based on your primary goals, you might want to reassess whether training your audience (showing them how to curate primary sources and make good LibGuides) or showcasing some LibGuides from your institution is what you want to share in the time of a conference presentation.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
