    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">GMT+8</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">71.3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">76.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">68.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">2</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">224</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1255</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Rudinsky, Joyce</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">technical critique of English based AI models that use image generation technologies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Interesting example of the limits of AI image generation and image processing. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I would only accept as a lightning talk. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">68</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1274</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Russell, John</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Image-based generative AI has a visual culture problem. This lightning talk will highlight an aspect of this problem by focusing on the mistakes that the DALL-E plugin for ChatGPT makes when rendering Chinese characters and calls for interventions in model development to address these issues.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a solid proposal for a lightning talk. It is timely and relevant to the conference&#039;s interests. While the recommendations are not novel, the problem outlined makes this proposal worthwhile.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">76</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1071</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Kijas, Anna E.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Author explores the issues and misinterpretations of LLMs, as well as algorithmic biases and racism in a case study focused on Chinese calligraphy.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The case study focused on the issues of LLMs and Chinese calligraphy is interesting and relevant to the conference theme. It would be helpful if the author could provide some theoretical framing in order to engage with current theories and scholarship and strengthen their argument for the importance of incorporating diverse cultural perspectives in the training of large AI models.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">70</ss:Data></Cell>
