    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">236</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1122</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Boyles, Christina</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This submission addresses both the existential and very real stressors of doing DH work in academia right now.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I think this proposal responds to both the existential and very real stressors of doing DH work in academia right now. I also think that the ACH conference is an excellent place to do this work, as we often cannot have these conversations within our own institutions and/or these topics may be relegated to chats with friends. By providing practical and applicable approaches to workshop attendees, the presenters can us think through how to address these issues effectively and systematically. I am greatly looking forward to this workshop!</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">100</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1248</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Knox, John Thomas</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This contribution describes challenges and pressures confronting DH practitioners today and some of the values and best practices that can be utilized to confront them.  </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a highly relevant topic and one that I think is likely to be of interest to conference participants. I am particularly interested to learn more about how individuals can develop toolkits to respond to institutional crises, and I think the focus on equipping participants for action is a strength. The contribution outlines a lot of items to be covered in the workshop, and one suggestion I have would be to consider whether all of the topics/activities can be covered in the time allotted.  </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">82</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1026</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Kerns, Halie Morgan</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Guiding participants on how to communicate and defend the values in their DH practice </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This workshop feels important and timely. I appreciate the breadth of practitioners involved and the topics it will touch on. From the description, it sounds like a workshop that everyone in the DH field can benefit from. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">100</ss:Data></Cell>
