    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">62.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">70.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">56.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">2</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">239</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1051</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Galvis, Elliot</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The paper seeks to explore the effect on (and relevance of) authenticity for creators and audiences with the introduction of content-generating AI tools.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposal seeks to engage with a fruitful and challenging element of creative production and reception with the introduction of AI. &#10;&#10;Overall, the proposal would benefit from greater specificity: with AI tools and media forms it will examine, with current and developing scholarship on these issues, and with the conceptual definitions it presents (i.e. clearly delineating &quot;traditional notions of authenticity.&quot;) The current proposal covers a lot of ground in very promising ways but would be stronger by focusing in on particular case studies for parsing AI-generated content and its relationship to &quot;authenticity.&quot;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The paper seems very broad in its focus at the moment, in ways that might be more speculative than ideal for a paper presentation.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">56</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1129</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Shaarawi, Jihan</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper focuses on the impact of generative AI technologies on creative sectors, specifically on issues of authenticity, authorship, and creativity. It examines how AI-generated content calls into question notions of authenticity and its implications for creators and audiences. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a very clear and relevant paper. I think it will be of great value to the discipline as it rapidly develops. &#10;It would be helpful to specify which generative AI technologies are being referred to. Are the discussions centered around text generation, image creation, music composition, or all of these? Providing a bit more detail here would clarify the scope. &#10;Additional clarity on methods would also help define how you&#039;re looking at ideas of authenticity and authorship.  </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">70</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1168</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Twani, Khanyisa</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">As scholarship grapples with multiple AI tools to engage on and with, the question of authenticity is indeed a vital question to keep in the fore of our minds.&#10;&#10;While the submission exemplifies an important concept in dealing with AI and digital transformation,  the framing and purposes are loosely expressed, making the scientific sense of the work unbalanced and verbose. The author could improve in terms of illustrating their framework and purpose more meticulously, and on a language point of view, write with shorter sentences for a more succinct explanation. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">60</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
