    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Improving the Conjecturator with Explanations</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">conjecture generation, generative AI, explanation</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;Experimental Humanities&#10;Global&#10;Contemporary&#10;artificial intelligence and machine learning&#10;curricular and pedagogical development and analysis&#10;text mining and analysis&#10;Computer science&#10;Informatics&#10;Linguistics&#10;Logic and epistemology</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Global</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">artificial intelligence and machine learning&#10;curricular and pedagogical development and analysis&#10;text mining and analysis</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Experimental Humanities&#10;Computer science&#10;Informatics&#10;Linguistics&#10;Logic and epistemology</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;Juola (2009) proposed a system (the Conjecturator) to enhance scholarly productivity by using data science and statistical techniques to analyze large databases, fill slots in templates, and check whether the resulting conjecture is true.  Unfortunately, this tool has not received much takeup, in part due to the difficulty of selecting conjectures from an essentially unlimited list of possibilities.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Recent advances in natural language processsing, and specifically the widespread availability of generative Large Language Models, allow computers to generate text to order on almost any given topic.  There are well-known issues with these LLMs, most notably that they are unreliable and will often provide information that is plausible but untrue.  However, in the context of providing reasons for hypotheses, this is not a problem, because causal hypotheses are not offered as true, but instead offered as ideas for discussion.  This tool will not diminish the role for human expertise and creativity, but will instead amplify it, because a human domain expert will still need to critically evaluate the proposed explanation and if necessary develop an alternative, in addition to providing the necessary supporting evidence.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Examples will be provided of template-generated hypotheses along with AI-generated examples of explanations and research methods.  I believe that this improvement can lead to better uptake of automatic conjecture generation and a substantial enhancement of scholarly productivity.  &lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Juola (2009) proposed a system (the Conjecturator) to enhance scholarly productivity by using data science and statistical techniques to analyze large databases, fill slots in templates, and check whether the resulting conjecture is true. Unfortunately, this tool has not received much takeup, in part due to the difficulty of selecting conjectures from an essentially unlimited list of possibilities.&#10;Recent advances in natural language processsing, and specifically the widespread availability of generative Large Language Models, allow computers to generate text to order on almost any given topic. There are well-known issues with these LLMs, most notably that they are unreliable and will often provide information that is plausible but untrue. However, in the context of providing reasons for hypotheses, this is not a problem, because causal hypotheses are not offered as true, but instead offered as ideas for discussion. This tool will not diminish the role for human expertise and creativity, but will instead amplify it, because a human domain expert will still need to critically evaluate the proposed explanation and if necessary develop an alternative, in addition to providing the necessary supporting evidence.&#10;Examples will be provided of template-generated hypotheses along with AI-generated examples of explanations and research methods. I believe that this improvement can lead to better uptake of automatic conjecture generation and a substantial enhancement of scholarly productivity.  </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
