    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Murphy, Emily Christina</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">University of British Columbia-Okanagan</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Canada</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North_America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"> </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">emily.murphy@ubc.ca</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">emily.murphy@ubc.ca, qilinliu@student.ubc.ca</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Murphy, Emily Christina;&#10;Liu, Qilin {Odessy}</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">emily.murphy@ubc.ca;&#10;qilinliu@student.ubc.ca</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">PST</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">60.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">68.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">54.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">245</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1275</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Kilbane, Matthew</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper employs a &quot;mixed manual and automated process&quot; to study--on the Goodreads platform--the emerging genre of graphic novel biographies, a genre for little served by existing scholarly methods. &#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper proposal has identified a fascinating archive and has made a compelling case that existing methods cannot do justice to this particular method. What needs development and clarification, it seems to me, is the &quot;mixed manual and automated process&quot; the author has developed in response to these challenges. What is this new method? And what are its larger implications for the study of digital literary practices? </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">54</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1127</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Alvarez, Martha Elizabeth</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This work presents a topic of significant relevance in the contemporary discussion about books, reading, and the training of readers through diverse platforms and social networks. Although this research is limited only to a platform called Goodreads, it can raise interesting findings on the topic in question, which is why the proposal is to be celebrated.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I consider it very important to emphasize the importance of digital platforms for the formation of readers and reading communities but without fetishizing technology. I find a greater interest in the technological part, which of course is important, but perhaps the focus should be on the symbolic content rather than the technical. Offering context of users interested in these platforms and comparing objectives and scope of other platforms used for the same purpose could greatly enrich the result of this work.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">68</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1118</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Forster, Chris</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper extends previous work GoodReads data (which is duly cited here), to the genre of &quot;graphic novel biographies.&quot; This is, the author claims, an especially interesting examination because unlike other genres (sci-fi, etc), this one remains inchoate and so poses unique challenges for analysis.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The prose of the this abstract is sometimes a little stilted (as in its first sentence). The author has clearly engaged with the existing scholarship, and this question (of an emergent genre) is absolutely interesting. I think the abstract could have benefited from some additional specifics about both the conclusions and the methods. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">58</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">6</ss:Data></Cell>
