    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Teaching Digital Communication in a Super Maximum Security Prison</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Digital Communication, Prison, Pedagogy, Access</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;postcolonial, decolonial, and anticolonial approaches&#10;Surveillance Studies&#10;North America&#10;Contemporary&#10;curricular and pedagogical development and analysis&#10;digital access, privacy, and ethics analysis&#10;Communication studies&#10;Education/Pedagogy</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">postcolonial, decolonial, and anticolonial approaches&#10;curricular and pedagogical development and analysis&#10;digital access, privacy, and ethics analysis</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Surveillance Studies&#10;Communication studies&#10;Education/Pedagogy</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Cal Poly Humboldt has launched a four-year BA in Communication at the highest security yard in Pelican Bay State Prison in rural northern California.  The program includes a junior-level Digital Communication course as part of the curriculum.  What are the complications and opportunities facilitating a Digital Humanities/Digital Communication course at a prison with severe limitations on student digital access and research/expression opportunities?  How do digital communication tools, methods and practices potentially amplify incarcerated student voices and weave abolitionist threads? &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;This is a facilitated roundtable discussion that will pose several questions and talk honestly about the experience of working in Pelican Bay State Prison with digital resources.  The purpose is to learn and share insights about best practices and strategies to support student engagement and learning.  &lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Cal Poly Humboldt has launched a four-year BA in Communication at the highest security yard in Pelican Bay State Prison in rural northern California. The program includes a junior-level Digital Communication course as part of the curriculum. What are the complications and opportunities facilitating a Digital Humanities/Digital Communication course at a prison with severe limitations on student digital access and research/expression opportunities? How do digital communication tools, methods and practices potentially amplify incarcerated student voices and weave abolitionist threads? &#10;This is a facilitated roundtable discussion that will pose several questions and talk honestly about the experience of working in Pelican Bay State Prison with digital resources. The purpose is to learn and share insights about best practices and strategies to support student engagement and learning.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
