    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">252</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1129</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Shaarawi, Jihan</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper focuses on algorithmic colonialism and its effects on the greater digital humanities discipline. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposal is extremely relevant to the topic of the conference. I appreciate the clear framing of what theory and concepts you will be working with. &#10;Further clarity on what you mean by &quot;invisible and nuanced&quot; mechanism would help you in the first part of your paper as you are introducing this topic to your audience. Clarifying the connection between the two parts of the presentation would also be useful. Explicitly state how understanding the concept of algorithmic colonialism can lead to explicit changes in the field.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">96</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1205</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Shukla, Nishanshi Atulkumar</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The main contribution of the submission is role of digital humanities in combating digital colonialism.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The outline of the presentation is stated well, but this does not frame an abstract of a paper. The abstract might benefit from reframing it and clearly stating how the argument stated in the title is made throughout the paper. Also, the current abstract sounds like a literature review and might benefit from a case study.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The abstract is comprised of possibilities of what &quot;can&quot; happen and be done. It does not resemble an abstract for an individual paper. Having said that, this is an important topic and can possibly turn into a good paper of framed well and supported by examples.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">70</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
