    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Academic/Industry collaboration to grow student participation in DH</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Publishing, peer-review, student scholarship, early-career researchers, product development</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;Global Digital Humanities&#10;Europe&#10;Contemporary&#10;digital publishing projects, systems, and methods&#10;text mining and analysis&#10;Education/Pedagogy&#10;Humanities Computing&#10;digital pedagogies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Europe</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">digital publishing projects, systems, and methods&#10;text mining and analysis&#10;digital pedagogies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Global Digital Humanities&#10;Education/Pedagogy&#10;Humanities Computing</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;In this talk, we explore an existing partnership between academia and industry to foster inclusivity in digital humanities. By introducing the Gale Research Showcase and the associated Project workflow in the &lt;em&gt;Gale Digital Scholar Lab&lt;/em&gt;, members of the product development team will explain the various testing methodologies and feedback mechanisms they used to ensure that academic partners were at the heart of these developments.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Gale has been working closely with digital humanities researchers for over 15 years in its role as one of the leading publishers of digitised primary sources. Since developing the first integrated text and data mining platform with &lt;em&gt;Gale Digital Scholar Lab&lt;/em&gt; in 2018, Gale’s archive platforms and the &lt;em&gt;Lab&lt;/em&gt; have developed to meet the needs of DH scholars and the wider humanities community as they have started to embrace DH methods.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;From the start, Gale has lowered the barriers to entry to digital humanities with the &lt;em&gt;Lab&lt;/em&gt;, providing more transparent, more accessible data and a no-code platform to make analysis projects available to all researchers, regardless of technical ability.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;This presentation will detail the iterative development process driven by academic feedback, particularly highlighting recent enhancements aimed at classroom integration and project-based learning. The 2024 launch of the Gale Research Showcase marks a significant step towards inclusivity, offering an open platform for early career researchers to gain experience in research review and publication. By showcasing practical outcomes and feedback from the DH community, we aim to discuss the broader implications of such industry-academic collaborations for making DH methodologies accessible to all humanities scholars, thus contributing to the inclusive ethos of ACH. &lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">In this talk, we explore an existing partnership between academia and industry to foster inclusivity in digital humanities. By introducing the Gale Research Showcase and the associated Project workflow in the Gale Digital Scholar Lab, members of the product development team will explain the various testing methodologies and feedback mechanisms they used to ensure that academic partners were at the heart of these developments.&#10;Gale has been working closely with digital humanities researchers for over 15 years in its role as one of the leading publishers of digitised primary sources. Since developing the first integrated text and data mining platform with Gale Digital Scholar Lab in 2018, Gale’s archive platforms and the Lab have developed to meet the needs of DH scholars and the wider humanities community as they have started to embrace DH methods.&#10;From the start, Gale has lowered the barriers to entry to digital humanities with the Lab, providing more transparent, more accessible data and a no-code platform to make analysis projects available to all researchers, regardless of technical ability.&#10;This presentation will detail the iterative development process driven by academic feedback, particularly highlighting recent enhancements aimed at classroom integration and project-based learning. The 2024 launch of the Gale Research Showcase marks a significant step towards inclusivity, offering an open platform for early career researchers to gain experience in research review and publication. By showcasing practical outcomes and feedback from the DH community, we aim to discuss the broader implications of such industry-academic collaborations for making DH methodologies accessible to all humanities scholars, thus contributing to the inclusive ethos of ACH.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
