    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">United States of America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">North_America</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"> </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">seanderson29@wisc.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">seanderson29@wisc.edu, jrinaldu@charlotte.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Anderson, Sydney Ellen;&#10;Rinalducci, Jenna</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">seanderson29@wisc.edu;&#10;jrinaldu@charlotte.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">US Central Time (Chicago)</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">56.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">62.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">46.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">256</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1265</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Arbuckle, Alyssa</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This proposed poster will discuss the findings of a survey on how to support faculty DH needs on campus. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This poster will be of interest to those who are seeking to develop more DH capacity at their own institutions. There is a focus on the role of the library in facilitating DH work. The proposal could be strengthened through a connection to existing, similar endeavours, and especially to the work of the Digital Library Federation. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">60</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1253</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Ford, Linsey</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This poster would focus on a library fellowship in digital humanities, created to support growing faculty interest. The fellow evaluated other digital humanities centers and spoke with stakeholders to determine tools and software used for related projects in order to address short and long-term goals for the library. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The project sounds interesting, but it could be better-focused on the conference theme. The proposal could also more explicitly engage with relevant scholarship and could better articulate the significance of the project&#039;s practical contribution to digital humanities.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">46</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1192</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Rodrigues, Liz</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This submission presents the results of fellowship research focused on developing a library strategy for supporting faculty doing digital humanities research. The research includes an environmental scan of digital humanities centers at regional and peer institutions and interviews with local campus stakeholders. The poster will present on this process, its findings, and the strategic recommendations that came out of it.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This research topic is highly compelling and likely to be of interest to many members of the ACH community, and I think that the library DH community in particular will welcome this work. The abstract is strong in its description of goal and method, but for the purposes of evaluation I would have liked to see more specifics about the results, ie, more of a sense of the overall argument that these findings suggest. Some examples of how such an argument could be communicated might be: what were common themes of expressed desires for services? Or, could the resulting recommendations be described in terms of broader categories like &quot;focus on training&quot; or &quot;offer support for student research assistants&quot;? Being a little more specific about these results might help with one other area of review criteria: engagement with prior scholarship in this area. Libraries have been investigating DH services for over a decade at least; does this work update, challenge, or expand these earlier findings?</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">62</ss:Data></Cell>
