    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">adriana.mata@my.utsa.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">audry686@hotmail.com</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">adriana.mata@my.utsa.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Mata, Adriana</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">adriana.mata@my.utsa.edu</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Central</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">83.3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">92.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">76.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">267</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1284</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Rousseau, Paulina</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This project focuses on grief experienced by survivors of loss, specifically of women of Mexican decent, through the intervention of the technological tool Omeka. It refers to numerous frameworks that can be used to disrupt the archive in hopes of aiding in the processing of grief. &#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a strong proposal that is clearly related to the conference focus, locates the topic within relevant frameworks, and explain how technological affordance can help to process grief. One aspect that could have been emphasized is whether this project already houses stories from others. If not, additionally information around project logistics may have been appreciated, however this is a very strong proposal. &#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This could be a lightning talk as well, however the proposal is strong to stand as an individual presentation, or as part of a panel. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">82</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1129</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Shaarawi, Jihan</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This panel deals with the ways that digital archives can help create a new space for collective grief.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is a powerful project with a clear sense of direction. The personal component creates an added layer of strength to this project. &#10;I would like to know more details on the methodology. What decisions are being made when it comes to what is being selected for the archive? What will the archive look like? How will it expand?</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">92</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1017</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Donea, Magdalena</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The practice of archiving a loved one&#039;s memory is enacted here as a communal, community, shared praxis, a counter-archive, accessible and inviting. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I&#039;m not sure how this would work as a poster from the author&#039;s end, but from an audience member&#039;s standpoint the opportunity to interact with the author directly and ask question - as a poster session tends to encourage - may make this a particularly poignant presentation. &#10;&#10;To be sure, I don&#039;t suggest this in lieu of the panel suggested; rather, if the panel is NOT accepted, I would definitely consider it as a poster.</ss:Data></Cell>
