    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">50.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">64.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">40.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">278</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1040</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Ferretti, Giulia</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I undoubtedly consider it useful to discuss new pedagogical frameworks in the humanities, which also reflect the advent of so-called artificial intelligence technologies. However, the research questions that would animate the discussion proposed are not clear. Nor is it clear how the audience would take part in the discussion.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">46</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1279</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Rogers, Katina L</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">As generative AI continues to spark interest and questions among scholars (and DH scholars in particular), a discussion on developing a related minor will likely be of significant interest to many.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Thank you for this submission. I think that the importance of discussing new minors in this field is significant, and would very much like to see this session move forward. At the same time, the abstract does not give me quite enough to go on—I don&#039;t have a sense of the stakes or challenges of setting up this minor. Instead, the abstract looks like copy from a website or registration page. That said, I think this is a valuable topic, and if the session is accepted I would recommend coming to greater clarity on what you hope to use the time for, and what you hope attendees come away with.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">64</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1226</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Spiro, Lisa</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This panel would discuss a new minor in on AI computing in the humanities at US college.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I&#039;m intrigued by the idea of offering a minor in AI in the context of arts and humanities, and the curriculum sounds engaging. The proposal would be stronger if it went beyond outlining the minor and highlighted some of the key questions to be examined by the panel. What motivated the development of this minor? How was the curriculum decided upon? The proposal lists 13 participants, which seems like too many for a panel.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">40</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">-1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Rejected</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s22"><Data ss:Type="DateTime">2024-09-07T17:42:26.000</Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1000</ss:Data></Cell>
