    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Knowledge Making of Pakistani Anglophone Fiction: A Visual and Thematic History</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Pakistani anglophone fiction, visual history, thematic history, accessibility, digitization, knowledge making, cultural preservation</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;Asia&#10;20th Century&#10;Contemporary&#10;data, object, and artifact preservation&#10;database creation, management, and analysis&#10;digital archiving&#10;Asian and Asian American Studies&#10;History</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Asia</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">20th Century&#10;Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">data, object, and artifact preservation&#10;database creation, management, and analysis&#10;digital archiving</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Asian and Asian American Studies&#10;History</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;Pakistani anglophone fiction spans over eight decades but its history is not catalogued in digital or any other form, thus arising the question of accessibility both for academia and people in general. Keeping this in view, I propose a project of developing a digital history of Pakistani anglophone fiction – visual and thematic history. The ongoing project proposes to develop the visual history in the first phase. For this purpose, I will collect data from different databases and publication houses to develop a spreadsheet. Following that I will use wordpress as a free website builder with limited extensions to showcase the visual history of Pakistani Anglophone fiction which will decolonize the knowledge making and help researchers to access the data effectively. Pakistan’s history has been diverse since its inception which resulted from Indian partition of 1947, military coupes, its own partition and making of Bangladesh, Islamization, political upheavals, war on terrorism and islamophobia  among many. In this phase of the project, I will exhibit the Pakistani anglophone fiction by categorizing it in various themes which may be multiple for one work at the same time. The purpose of the project is to make knowledge of Pakistani history which is equally and easily accessible to Pakistanis and the people around the globe. This project also has a purpose to preserve diverse ethnic cultures through this project.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keywords:&lt;/strong&gt; Pakistani anglophone fiction, visual history, thematic history, accessibility, digitization, knowledge making, cultural preservation&lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Pakistani anglophone fiction spans over eight decades but its history is not catalogued in digital or any other form, thus arising the question of accessibility both for academia and people in general. Keeping this in view, I propose a project of developing a digital history of Pakistani anglophone fiction – visual and thematic history. The ongoing project proposes to develop the visual history in the first phase. For this purpose, I will collect data from different databases and publication houses to develop a spreadsheet. Following that I will use wordpress as a free website builder with limited extensions to showcase the visual history of Pakistani Anglophone fiction which will decolonize the knowledge making and help researchers to access the data effectively. Pakistan’s history has been diverse since its inception which resulted from Indian partition of 1947, military coupes, its own partition and making of Bangladesh, Islamization, political upheavals, war on terrorism and islamophobia among many. In this phase of the project, I will exhibit the Pakistani anglophone fiction by categorizing it in various themes which may be multiple for one work at the same time. The purpose of the project is to make knowledge of Pakistani history which is equally and easily accessible to Pakistanis and the people around the globe. This project also has a purpose to preserve diverse ethnic cultures through this project.&#10;Keywords: Pakistani anglophone fiction, visual history, thematic history, accessibility, digitization, knowledge making, cultural preservation</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
