    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Li, Yunxin</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This project intends to fill a gap in the digital preservation of Pakistani Anglophone Fiction. The author is willing to invest much time in collecting and presenting data.  </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This project intends to fill a gap in the digital preservation of Pakistani Anglophone Fiction. The author is willing to invest much time in collecting and presenting data. &#10;&#10;While the author&#039;s effort is admirable, the current abstract leaves me with a few questions, and I hope that the author can address them in their presentation. First, why is the scope limited to Anglophone fiction, not Pakistani fiction written in local languages? How does the scope affect research on the history of Pakistani fiction? What databases and publication houses will the author rely on, and what are their biases? Second, how did the political and social changes in Pakistani history affect Pakistani Anglophone fiction, or vice versa? Third, what concrete methods or tools in WordPress will the author use to present and analyze the data? Will the author use other tools as well, such as text analysis tools?</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">54</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1229</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Adal, Raja</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This project proposes to create a digital history of Pakistani Anglophone fiction.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Why are you focusing only on Anglophone literature in Pakistan?  This needs a rationale.  It would also be useful to contextualize Anglophone fiction in Pakistan in the context of all fiction in Pakistan.  Also, what does a digital history look like?</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I don&#039;t really see the value of focusing only an Anglophone Pakistani literature, but others may.  If you have room for poster presentations, then why not.  You may want to encourage the presenter to explain why Anglophone literature is in itself a useful category.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">48</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1046</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Wu, Menghang</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">The main contribution of this research is developing a digital visual history of Pakistani anglophone fiction, aiming at enhancing accessibility for academia and the general public. This project will decolonize knowledge by systematically cataloging and showcasing the thematic diversity of Pakistani anglophone literature, preserving its cultural heritage and making it easily accessible globally.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This is an interesting research idea. Could you engage relative scholarship more critically and deeply? How do visual history and accessibility help promote decolonization? This is a very ambitious project. Which part do you present most in this conference? Try to be specific in the later abstract version, maybe just answer the question of how exactly it contributes to decolonization. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">80</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">-1</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Rejected</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s22"><Data ss:Type="DateTime">2024-09-07T17:43:05.000</Data></Cell>
