    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Radical Activism: the Role of Social Media in Political Mobilization in Nigeria</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Political Mobilization, Radical Activism, Social Media, YouTube, Democracy</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English&#10;Africa&#10;Contemporary&#10;digital activism and advocacy&#10;African American/Black Studies&#10;Cultural studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">English</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Africa</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Contemporary</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">digital activism and advocacy</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">African American/Black Studies&#10;Cultural studies</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">&lt;p&gt;This paper explores the context of social media in the quest for good governance in Nigeria through the political mobilization of the masses. In appraising the revolutionary aesthetics of this clamor for a new order of sociopolitical systems in Nigeria through the lens of social media, the paper focuses on the contributions made by Aisha Yesufu, a prominent pro-democracy activist, in launching the presidential campaign of the lesser-known Peter Obi into the national limelight and significantly positioning him as a strong candidate for the 2023 general elections. Drawing from a content analysis of the rhetorical strategies employed in selected videos on Aisha Yesufu&#039;s YouTube channel, the paper assesses the impact of activism propelled by social media in Nigeria and concludes that social media is a potent instrument for igniting radical activism and mobilizing support towards effective leadership in Nigeria in the digital age.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This paper explores the context of social media in the quest for good governance in Nigeria through the political mobilization of the masses. In appraising the revolutionary aesthetics of this clamor for a new order of sociopolitical systems in Nigeria through the lens of social media, the paper focuses on the contributions made by Aisha Yesufu, a prominent pro-democracy activist, in launching the presidential campaign of the lesser-known Peter Obi into the national limelight and significantly positioning him as a strong candidate for the 2023 general elections. Drawing from a content analysis of the rhetorical strategies employed in selected videos on Aisha Yesufu&#039;s YouTube channel, the paper assesses the impact of activism propelled by social media in Nigeria and concludes that social media is a potent instrument for igniting radical activism and mobilizing support towards effective leadership in Nigeria in the digital age.</ss:Data></Cell>
