    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">3</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">78.7</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">90.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">62.0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">2</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">0.0000</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">297</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1258</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Maselli, Matteo</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Despite the proposal being interesting and the objectives set being of definite importance and utility, the methodologies for the implementation of the database of Chinese Buddhist publications from the Republican era (1912-1949) are not clearly explained. It is recommended to clarify this point, as it is central to the acceptance of the proposal.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">62</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1259</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Li, Yunxin</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This project expands an existing database of Chinese Buddhist publications by adding more entries on the republican era. It preserves valuable historical artifacts and facilitates future scholarly research on Buddhism.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This project expands an existing database of Chinese Buddhist publications by adding more entries on the republican era. It preserves valuable historical artifacts and facilitates future scholarly research on Buddhism. It is a very worthwhile effort.&#10;&#10;For those who are unfamiliar with the original database, I would recommend that the author introduce the scope and the structure of the database before talking about the new material. It is also worth mentioning how the data from the republican period is different from Buddhist publications in earlier periods so that users can better use them for research. &#10;&#10;</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">90</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1123</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Evans, Daniel</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This poster looks to enhance an existing database with additional metadata derived from newly digitized sources. The hope is that these enhancements will facilitate future research on Buddhism in China during the early 20th Century.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This poster provides a clear framework for enhancing an existing database with additional metadata tags. While it does provide some implications or possible use-cases that can be derived from this work, the larger poster would benefit from more concrete examples of ways in which these newly digitized sources will enhance future scholarship. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
