    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">301</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1306</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Yuan, Miaotong</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Theoretical thinking is perfectly reflected in artistic expression.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Interesting topic, nicely designed and nicely structured. Looking forward to visit this piece online.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">84</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1239</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Kunnuji, Joseph</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This abstract examines an orchestra performance without an audience to demonstrate the complexities surrounding meaning-making and accessibility within sound studies. The manipulation of what is heard through technology in the study is intriguing and makes one look forward to experiencing the presentation.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">This abstract examines an orchestra performance without an audience to demonstrate the complexities surrounding meaning-making and accessibility within sound studies. The manipulation of what is heard through technology in the study is intriguing and makes one look forward to experiencing the presentation. The abstract can be improved by more clearly highlighting the methodologies and scholarly works the study engages with.</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String"></ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">78</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">1255</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">Rudinsky, Joyce</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">uses synthesized sound to give an audience an alternative audio aesthetic to raise issues of accessibility</ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I would like to read how this project confronts ableism in assistive hearing design. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="String">I don&#039;t think this has much art relevance. I don&#039;t think an audience will get much out of it. </ss:Data></Cell>
    <Cell><ss:Data ss:Type="Number">40</ss:Data></Cell>
